    "agePeak_months": [360, 600],
    "note": "Acquired clonal hematopoietic stem cell disorder caused by PIG-A gene mutation, leading to deficient GPI-anchored proteins (CD55, CD59) on RBC surface. Results in complement-mediated intravascular hemolysis. Classic triad: hemolytic anemia, hemoglobinuria (especially nocturnal), and venous thrombosis. Jaundice is common from hemolysis. Can present with abdominal pain, dysphagia, and erectile dysfunction. Associated with aplastic anemia and MDS.",
